in Eclipse. When the task is not there - the dialogue can be exited.

I think the problem is that Discovery Profile control combobox field is (empty).
How do you managed to get it empty is this standard or managed make project?
Maybe this is installation issue or old workspace. please check this.
In my installation it allways filled with 2 values from which I can choose.

It is standard make project (non-managed). The Eclipse 3.1 installation is fresh
but I had used CDT 3.0 release candidates before upgrading to the full one.

Is there any preferences I need to clear in one of the workplace for CDT tools?

The C++ project was created from scratch - using existing C++ sources.
Try to launch eclipse from command line by typing: eclipse -clean

Is there any other way to clean CDT stuff? I have loads of Java projects in my
work environment and I don't want to loose all config for them.

By doing this you only reset osgi plugin configuration and tell eclipse to 
rescan existing plugins.
This will not affect workspace configuration.
Nop - eclipse -clean didn't helped. Still no profiles.
This was never reproduced and does not seem to currently be an issue.  Please re-test with CDT 4.0 and see if it's still an issue.  If it's still an issue please reopen this bug.
